olive oil
1 carrot
1 packet Baby Leaves
½ cucumber
2 clove garlic
1 packet black beans
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
20 g butter
¼ cup water
1 packet passata
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 packet Corn Chips
1 packet pork mince

• Grate carrot. Roughly chop baby leaves. Thinly slice cucumber (see ingredients). Finely chop garlic. Drain and rinse half the black beans.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook pork mince and carrot, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add drained and rinsed black beans, garlic and All-American spice blend and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.

• Stir in the butter, water, passata and vegetable stock powder, until combined and slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes.
• Season to taste.

• Meanwhile, combine baby leaves, cucumber and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil in a medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper.

• Divide American-style pork and black bean chilli between bowls. Sprinkle over shredded Cheddar cheese.
• Top with cucumber salad and Greek-style yoghurt.
• Serve with corn chips. Enjoy!